author: COMSOL
description: This is an example of pressure-driven flow and electrophoresis in a microchannel system. Focusing is obtained through pressure-driven flow of the sample and buffer solution, which confines the sample in the focusing channel. When steady state has been obtained, the pressure driven flow is turned off and an electric field is applied, which drives the dissociated sample ions through the injection channel.
label: electrokinetic_valve.mph
name: root
